01340     return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001180044000430ull);
01341 }
01342 #else
01343 #define CVMX_PKI_TAG_SECRET (CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001180044000430ull))
01344 #endif
01345 #if CVMX_ENABLE_CSR_ADDRESS_CHECKING
01346 #define CVMX_PKI_X2P_REQ_OFL CVMX_PKI_X2P_REQ_OFL_FUNC()
01347 static inline uint64_t CVMX_PKI_X2P_REQ_OFL_FUNC(void)
01348 {
01349     if (!(OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN73XX) || OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX) || OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN78XX_PASS1_X) || OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CNF75XX)))
01350         cvmx_warn("CVMX_PKI_X2P_REQ_OFL not supported on this chip\n");
01351     return CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001180044000038ull);
01352 }
01353 #else
01354 #define CVMX_PKI_X2P_REQ_OFL (CVMX_ADD_IO_SEG(0x0001180044000038ull))
01355 #endif

01577 union cvmx_pki_buf_ctl {

01580 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01581     uint64_t reserved_11_63               : 53;
01582     uint64_t fpa_wait                     : 1;  /**< Policy when FPA runs out of buffers:
01583                                                          0 = Drop the remainder of the packet requesting the buffer, and set
01584                                                          PKI_WQE_S[ERRLEV,OPCODE] to PKI_ERRLEV_E::RE,PKI_OPCODE_E::RE_MEMOUT.
01585                                                          1 = Wait until buffers become available, only dropping packets if buffering ahead of PKI
01586                                                          fills. This may lead to head-of-line blocking of packets on other Auras. */

01590                                                          data; when it is clear to 0, the PKI works normally, buffering the received packet data. */
01591     uint64_t reserved_3_4                 : 2;
01592     uint64_t pbp_en                       : 1;  /**< Bpid enable. When set, enables the sending of bpid level backpressure to the input
01593                                                          interface.
01594                                                          The application should not de-assert this bit after asserting it. The receivers of this
01595                                                          bit may have been put into backpressure mode and can only be released by PKI informing
01596                                                          them that the backpressure has been released. */
01597     uint64_t reserved_1_1                 : 1;
01598     uint64_t pki_en                       : 1;  /**< PKI enable. When set to 1, enables the operation of the PKI. When clear to 0, the PKI
01599                                                          asserts backpressure on all ports. */
01600 #else
01601     uint64_t pki_en                       : 1;
01602     uint64_t reserved_1_1                 : 1;
01603     uint64_t pbp_en                       : 1;
01604     uint64_t reserved_3_4                 : 2;
01605     uint64_t pkt_off                      : 1;
01606     uint64_t reserved_6_8                 : 3;
01607     uint64_t fpa_cac_dis                  : 1;
01608     uint64_t fpa_wait                     : 1;
01609     uint64_t reserved_11_63               : 53;
01610 #endif
01611     } s;

01767 /**
01768  * cvmx_pki_cl#_pcam#_action#
01769  *
01770  * This register configures the result side of the PCAM. PKI hardware is opaque as to the use
01771  * of the 32 bits of CAM result.
01772  *
01773  * For each legal j and k, PKI_CL(i)_PCAM(j)_ACTION(k) must be configured identically for i=0..1.
01774  *
01775  * With the current parse engine code:
01776  *
01777  * Action performed based on PCAM lookup using the PKI_CL()_PCAM()_TERM() and
01778  * PKI_CL()_PCAM()_MATCH() registers.
01779  *
01780  * If lookup data matches no PCAM entries, then no action takes place. No matches indicates
01781  * normal parsing will continue.
01782  *
01783  * If data matches multiple PCAM entries, PKI_WQE_S[ERRLEV,OPCODE] of the processed packet may
01784  * be set to PKI_ERRLEV_E::RE,PKI_OPCODE_E::RE_PKIPCAM and the PKI_CL()_INT[PCAM_CONF] error
01785  * interrupt is signaled.  Once a conflict is detected, the PCAM state is unpredictable and is
01786  * required to be fully reconfigured before further valid processing can take place.
01787  */
01788 union cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_actionx {
01789     uint64_t u64;
01790     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_actionx_s {
01791 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01792     uint64_t reserved_31_63               : 33;
01793     uint64_t pmc                          : 7;  /**< Parse mode change. Where to resume parsing after applying the scan offset (if any) as bit
01794                                                          mask of which parse engine steps to no longer process:
01795                                                          _ <0> = LA (L2).
01796                                                          _ <1> = LB (Custom).
01797                                                          _ <2> = LC (L3).
01798                                                          _ <3> = LD (Virt).
01799                                                          _ <4> = LE (IL3).
01800                                                          _ <5> = LF (L4).
01801                                                          _ <6> = LG (Custom/Application-specific relative to C, D, E, or F).
01802                                                          Typically PMC is 0x0 to indicate no parse mode change.  Must be zero for invalid
01803                                                          entries, or for TERMs that do not allow a parse mode change as specified in the
01804                                                          PMC column of the PKI_PCAM_TERM_E table.
01805                                                          Typical values for PMC<5:0> are:
01806                                                            0x0 = no change in parsing.
01807                                                            0x1 = Skip further LA parsing; start LB parsing.
01808                                                            0x3 = Skip further LA/LB parsing; start LC parsing.
01809                                                            0x7 = Skip further LA-LC parsing; start LD parsing.
01810                                                            0x38 = Skip LD, LE, LF parsing.
01811                                                            0x3F = Skip all parsing; no further packet inspection.
01812                                                          The typical use of PMC<5:0> being nonzero is for Ethertypes or custom headers
01813                                                          to indicate non-IP follows that Ethertype/custom header. This corresponds to use
01814                                                          only with PKI_PCAM_TERM_E::ETHTYPE0..3, and PKI_PCAM_TERM_E::L2_CUSTOM.
01815                                                          Independently PMC<6> may be set to disable LG (LG_CUSTOM) parsing. */
01816     uint64_t style_add                    : 8;  /**< Resulting interim style adder. If this CAM entry matches, the value to add to the current
01817                                                          style (may wrap around through 256). Must be zero for invalid entries. */
01818     uint64_t pf                           : 3;  /**< Parse flag to set. Specifies the parse flag to set when entry matches, see PCAM actions
01819                                                          may also specify setting one of four user flags in the generated work queue entry,
01820                                                          PKI_WQE_S[PF1] through PKI_WQE_S[PF4]. These flags are not used by hardware; they are
01821                                                          intended to
01822                                                          indicate to software that exceptional handling may be required, such as the presence of an
01823                                                          encrypted packet:
01824                                                          _ 0x0 = no change.
01825                                                          _ 0x1 = Set PKI_WQE_S[PF1].
01826                                                          _ 0x2 = Set PKI_WQE_S[PF2].
01827                                                          _ 0x3 = Set PKI_WQE_S[PF3].
01828                                                          _ 0x4 = Set PKI_WQE_S[PF4].
01829                                                          _ else = reserved.
01830                                                          Must be zero for invalid entries. */
01831     uint64_t setty                        : 5;  /**< Set pointer type. If nonzero, indicates the layer type to be set as described under
01832                                                          PKI_PCAM_TERM_E. Values are enumerated by PKI_LTYPE_E. Must be zero for invalid entries.
01833                                                          The PKI_PCAM_TERM_E table enumerates legal/common SETTY values. */
01834     uint64_t advance                      : 8;  /**< Relative number of bytes to advance scan pointer when entry matches.
01835                                                          Must be even. Must be zero for invalid entries and for TERMs that do not allow
01836                                                          an advance as specified in the PKI_PCAM_TERM_E table. */
01837 #else
01838     uint64_t advance                      : 8;
01839     uint64_t setty                        : 5;
01840     uint64_t pf                           : 3;
01841     uint64_t style_add                    : 8;
01842     uint64_t pmc                          : 7;
01843     uint64_t reserved_31_63               : 33;
01844 #endif
01845     } s;
01846     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_actionx_s   cn73xx;
01847     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_actionx_s   cn78xx;
01848     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_actionx_s   cn78xxp1;
01849     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_actionx_s   cnf75xx;
01850 };
01851 typedef union cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_actionx cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_actionx_t;

01853 /**
01854  * cvmx_pki_cl#_pcam#_match#
01855  *
01856  * This register configures the match side of the PCAM. PKI hardware is opaque as to the use
01857  * of the 32 bits of CAM data.
01858  *
01859  * For each legal j and k, PKI_CL(i)_PCAM(j)_MATCH(k) must be configured identically for i=0..1.
01860  */
01861 union cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_matchx {
01862     uint64_t u64;
01863     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_matchx_s {
01864 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01865     uint64_t data1                        : 32; /**< See [DATA0]. */
01866     uint64_t data0                        : 32; /**< The packet data to compare against. Bits may be ignored in comparison based on [DATA0] and
01867                                                          [DATA1]. If the entry matches, PKI_CL()_PCAM()_ACTION() will determine the
01868                                                          action to be taken. See PKI_PCAM_TERM_E for comparison bit definitions.
01869                                                          The field value is ternary, where each bit matches as follows:
01870                                                          _ [DATA1]<n>=0, [DATA0]<n>=0: Always match; data<n> don't care.
01871                                                          _ [DATA1]<n>=0, [DATA0]<n>=1: Match when data<n> == 0.
01872                                                          _ [DATA1]<n>=1, [DATA0]<n>=0: Match when data<n> == 1.
01873                                                          _ [DATA1]<n>=1, [DATA0]<n>=1: Reserved. */
01874 #else
01875     uint64_t data0                        : 32;
01876     uint64_t data1                        : 32;
01877 #endif
01878     } s;
01879     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_matchx_s    cn73xx;
01880     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_matchx_s    cn78xx;
01881     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_matchx_s    cn78xxp1;
01882     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_matchx_s    cnf75xx;
01883 };
01884 typedef union cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_matchx cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_matchx_t;

01886 /**
01887  * cvmx_pki_cl#_pcam#_term#
01888  *
01889  * This register configures the match side of the PCAM. PKI hardware is opaque as to the use
01890  * of the 16 bits of CAM data; the split between TERM and STYLE is defined by the
01891  * parse engine.
01892  *
01893  * For each legal j and k, PKI_CL(i)_PCAM(j)_TERM(k) must be configured identically for i=0..1.
01894  */
01895 union cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_termx {
01896     uint64_t u64;
01897     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_termx_s {
01898 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01899     uint64_t valid                        : 1;  /**< Valid. */
01900     uint64_t reserved_48_62               : 15;
01901     uint64_t term1                        : 8;  /**< See [TERM0]. */
01902     uint64_t style1                       : 8;  /**< See [STYLE0]. */
01903     uint64_t reserved_16_31               : 16;
01904     uint64_t term0                        : 8;  /**< Comparison type. Enumerated by PKI_PCAM_TERM_E. The field value is ternary, where each
01905                                                          bit matches as follows:
01906                                                          _ [TERM1]<n>=0, [TERM0]<n>=0: Always match; data<n> don't care.
01907                                                          _ [TERM1]<n>=0, [TERM0]<n>=1: Match when data<n> == 0.
01908                                                          _ [TERM1]<n>=1, [TERM0]<n>=0: Match when data<n> == 1.
01909                                                          _ [TERM1]<n>=1, [TERM0]<n>=1: Reserved. */
01910     uint64_t style0                       : 8;  /**< Previous interim style. The style that must have been calculated by the port
01911                                                          PKI_CL()_PKIND()_STYLE[STYLE] or as modified by previous CAM hits's
01912                                                          PKI_CL()_PCAM()_ACTION()[STYLE_ADD]. This is used to form AND style matches.
01913                                                          The field value is ternary, where each bit matches as follows:
01914                                                          _ [STYLE1]<n>=0, [STYLE0]<n>=0: Always match; data<n> don't care.
01915                                                          _ [STYLE1]<n>=0, [STYLE0]<n>=1: Match when data<n> == 0.
01916                                                          _ [STYLE1]<n>=1, [STYLE0]<n>=0: Match when data<n> == 1.
01917                                                          _ [STYLE1]<n>=1, [STYLE0]<n>=1: Reserved. */
01918 #else
01919     uint64_t style0                       : 8;
01920     uint64_t term0                        : 8;
01921     uint64_t reserved_16_31               : 16;
01922     uint64_t style1                       : 8;
01923     uint64_t term1                        : 8;
01924     uint64_t reserved_48_62               : 15;
01925     uint64_t valid                        : 1;
01926 #endif
01927     } s;
01928     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_termx_s     cn73xx;
01929     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_termx_s     cn78xx;
01930     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_termx_s     cn78xxp1;
01931     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pcamx_termx_s     cnf75xx;

01935 /**
01936  * cvmx_pki_cl#_pkind#_cfg
01937  *
01938  * This register is inside PKI_CL()_PKIND()_KMEM(). These CSRs are used only by
01939  * the PKI parse engine.
01940  *
01941  * For each legal j, PKI_CL(i)_PKIND(j)_CFG must be configured identically for i=0..1.
01942  */
01943 union cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_cfg {
01944     uint64_t u64;
01945     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_cfg_s {
01946 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01947     uint64_t reserved_11_63               : 53;
01948     uint64_t lg_custom_layer              : 3;  /**< Layer G custom match enable.
01949                                                          0x0 = Disable custom LG header extraction
01950                                                          0x1 = Enable custom LG header extraction after layer C.
01951                                                          0x2 = Enable custom LG header extraction after layer D.
01952                                                          0x3 = Enable custom LG header extraction after layer E.
01953                                                          0x4 = Enable custom LG header extraction after layer F.
01954                                                          0x5-0x7 = Reserved. */
01955     uint64_t fcs_pres                     : 1;  /**< FCS present.
01956                                                          0 = FCS not present. FCS may not be checked nor stripped.
01957                                                          1 = FCS present; the last four bytes of the packet are part of the FCS and may not be
01958                                                          considered part of a IP, TCP or other header for length error checks.
01959                                                          When either PKI_CL()_STYLE()_CFG[FCS_CHK or FCS_STRIP] are set, the
01960                                                          corresponding [FCS_PRES] must be set. */
01961     uint64_t mpls_en                      : 1;  /**< Enable MPLS parsing.
01962                                                          0 = Any MPLS labels are ignored, but may be handled by custom Ethertype PCAM matchers.
01963                                                          1 = MPLS label stacks are parsed and skipped over. */
01964     uint64_t inst_hdr                     : 1;  /**< INST header. When set, a PKI_INST_HDR_S is present PKI_CL()_PKIND()_SKIP[INST_SKIP]
01965                                                          bytes into the packet received by PKI. */
01966     uint64_t lg_custom                    : 1;  /**< Reserved. */
01967     uint64_t fulc_en                      : 1;  /**< Enable Fulcrum tag parsing.
01968                                                          0 = Any Fulcrum header is ignored.
01969                                                          1 = Fulcrum header is parsed.
01970                                                          [FULC_EN] must be clear when any of [HG_EN,HG2_EN,DSA_EN] are set. */
01971     uint64_t dsa_en                       : 1;  /**< Enable DSA parsing.
01972                                                          0 = Any DSA header is ignored.
01973                                                          1 = DSA is parsed.
01974                                                          [DSA_EN] must be clear when any of [HG_EN,HG2_EN,FULC_EN] are set. */
01975     uint64_t hg2_en                       : 1;  /**< Enable HiGig 2 parsing.
01976                                                          0 = Any HiGig2 header is ignored.
01977                                                          1 = HiGig2 is parsed.
01978                                                          [HG2_EN] must be clear when any of [HG_EN,FULC_EN,DSA_EN] is set. */
01979     uint64_t hg_en                        : 1;  /**< Enable HiGig parsing.
01980                                                          0 = Any HiGig header is ignored.
01981                                                          1 = HiGig is parsed.
01982                                                          [HG_EN] must be clear when any of [HG2_EN,FULC_EN,DSA_EN] is set. */
01983 #else
01984     uint64_t hg_en                        : 1;
01985     uint64_t hg2_en                       : 1;
01986     uint64_t dsa_en                       : 1;
01987     uint64_t fulc_en                      : 1;
01988     uint64_t lg_custom                    : 1;
01989     uint64_t inst_hdr                     : 1;
01990     uint64_t mpls_en                      : 1;
01991     uint64_t fcs_pres                     : 1;
01992     uint64_t lg_custom_layer              : 3;
01993     uint64_t reserved_11_63               : 53;
01994 #endif
01995     } s;
01996     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_cfg_s      cn73xx;
01997     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_cfg_s      cn78xx;
01998     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_cfg_s      cn78xxp1;

02003 /**
02004  * cvmx_pki_cl#_pkind#_kmem#
02005  *
02006  * This register initializes the KMEM, which initializes the parse engine state for each
02007  * pkind. These CSRs are used only by the PKI parse engine.
02008  *
02009  * Inside the KMEM are the following parse engine registers. These registers are the
02010  * preferred access method for software:
02011  * * PKI_CL()_PKIND()_CFG.
02012  * * PKI_CL()_PKIND()_STYLE.
02013  * * PKI_CL()_PKIND()_SKIP.
02014  * * PKI_CL()_PKIND()_L2_CUSTOM.
02015  * * PKI_CL()_PKIND()_LG_CUSTOM.
02016  *
02017  * To avoid overlapping addresses, these aliases have address bit 20 set in contrast to
02018  * this register; the PKI address decoder ignores bit 20 when accessing
02019  * PKI_CL()_PKIND()_KMEM().
02020  *
02021  * Software must reload the PKI_CL()_PKIND()_KMEM() registers upon the detection of
02022  * PKI_ECC_INT0[KMEM_SBE] or PKI_ECC_INT0[KMEM_DBE].
02023  *
02024  * For each legal j and k value, PKI_CL(i)_PKIND(j)_KMEM(k) must be configured
02025  * identically for i=0..1.
02026  */
02027 union cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_kmemx {
02028     uint64_t u64;
02029     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_kmemx_s {
02030 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02031     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
02032     uint64_t data                         : 16; /**< RAM data at given address. */
02033 #else
02034     uint64_t data                         : 16;
02035     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
02036 #endif
02037     } s;

02142 /**
02143  * cvmx_pki_cl#_pkind#_style
02144  *
02145  * This register is inside PKI_CL()_PKIND()_KMEM(). These CSRs are used only by
02146  * the PKI parse engine.
02147  *
02148  * For each legal j, PKI_CL(i)_PKIND(j)_STYLE must be configured identically for i=0..1.
02149  */
02150 union cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_style {
02151     uint64_t u64;
02152     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_style_s {
02153 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02154     uint64_t reserved_15_63               : 49;
02155     uint64_t pm                           : 7;  /**< Initial parse mode. Bit mask of which steps the parse engine should perform, refer
02156                                                          to Parse Mode:
02157                                                          _ <0> = LA - Layer A (Ethernet dest+src, Higig/Fulcrum/DSA).
02158                                                          _ <1> = LB - Layer B (Ethertype/VLAN, MPLS/ARP/REVARP/SNAP).
02159                                                          _ <2> = LC - Layer C (Outer IPv4 or IPv6).
02160                                                          _ <3> = LD - Layer D (Geneve/VXLAN/VXLANGPE/NVGRE).
02161                                                          _ <4> = LE - Layer E (Inner IPv4 or IPv6).
02162                                                          _ <5> = LF - Layer F (UDP, TCP, SCTP, IPCOMP, IPSEC ESP/AH, GRE).
02163                                                          _ <6> = LG - Layer G (Custom/Application).
02164                                                          The legal values are:
02165                                                          _ 0x0 = Parse LA..LG.
02166                                                          _ 0x1 = Parse LB..LG.
02167                                                          _ 0x3 = Parse LC..LG.
02168                                                          _ 0x7F = Parse none and error check none of LA..LG.
02169                                                          _ else = Reserved. */
02170     uint64_t style                        : 8;  /**< Initial style. Initial style number for packets on this port, will remain as final style
02171                                                          if no PCAM entries match the packet. Note only 64 final styles exist, the upper two bits
02172                                                          will only be used for PCAM matching. */
02173 #else
02174     uint64_t style                        : 8;
02175     uint64_t pm                           : 7;
02176     uint64_t reserved_15_63               : 49;
02177 #endif
02178     } s;
02179     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_style_s    cn73xx;
02180     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_style_s    cn78xx;
02181     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_style_s    cn78xxp1;
02182     struct cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_style_s    cnf75xx;
02183 };
02184 typedef union cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_style cvmx_pki_clx_pkindx_style_t;

02186 /**
02187  * cvmx_pki_cl#_smem#
02188  *
02189  * This register initializes the SMEM, which configures the parse engine. These CSRs
02190  * are used by the PKI parse engine and other PKI hardware.
02191  *
02192  * Inside the SMEM are the following parse engine registers. These registers are the
02193  * preferred access method for software:
02194  * * PKI_CL()_STYLE()_CFG
02195  * * PKI_CL()_STYLE()_CFG2
02196  * * PKI_CL()_STYLE()_ALG
02197  *
02198  * To avoid overlapping addresses, these aliases have address bit 20 set in contrast to
02199  * this register; the PKI address decoder ignores bit 20 when accessing
02200  * PKI_CL()_SMEM().
02201  *
02202  * Software must reload the PKI_CL()_SMEM() registers upon the detection of
02203  * PKI_CL()_ECC_INT[SMEM_SBE] or PKI_CL()_ECC_INT[SMEM_DBE].
02204  *
02205  * For each legal j, PKI_CL(i)_SMEM(j) must be configured identically for i=0..1.
02206  */
02207 union cvmx_pki_clx_smemx {
02208     uint64_t u64;
02209     struct cvmx_pki_clx_smemx_s {
02210 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02211     uint64_t reserved_32_63               : 32;
02212     uint64_t data                         : 32; /**< RAM data at given address. */
02213 #else
02214     uint64_t data                         : 32;
02215     uint64_t reserved_32_63               : 32;
02216 #endif
02217     } s;
02218     struct cvmx_pki_clx_smemx_s           cn73xx;
02219     struct cvmx_pki_clx_smemx_s           cn78xx;
02220     struct cvmx_pki_clx_smemx_s           cn78xxp1;
02221     struct cvmx_pki_clx_smemx_s           cnf75xx;
02222 };
02223 typedef union cvmx_pki_clx_smemx cvmx_pki_clx_smemx_t;

02254  *
02255  * For each legal j, PKI_CL(i)_STYLE(j)_ALG must be configured identically for i=0..1.
02256  */
02257 union cvmx_pki_clx_stylex_alg {
02258     uint64_t u64;
02259     struct cvmx_pki_clx_stylex_alg_s {
02260 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02261     uint64_t reserved_32_63               : 32;
02262     uint64_t tt                           : 2;  /**< SSO tag type to schedule to, enumerated by SSO_TT_E. */
02263     uint64_t apad_nip                     : 3;  /**< Value for PKI_WQE_S[APAD] when packet is not IP. */
02264     uint64_t qpg_qos                      : 3;  /**< Algorithm to select QoS field in QPG calculation. Enumerated by PKI_QPGQOS_E. */
02265     uint64_t qpg_port_sh                  : 3;  /**< Number of bits to shift port number in QPG calculation. */
02266     uint64_t qpg_port_msb                 : 4;  /**< MSB to take from port number in QPG calculation.
02267                                                          0 = Exclude port number from QPG.
02268                                                          4 = Include port<3:0>.
02269                                                          8 = Include port<7:0>.
02270                                                          _ All other values reserved. */
02271     uint64_t reserved_11_16               : 6;
02272     uint64_t tag_vni                      : 1;  /**< When NVGRE/VXLAN/VXLANGPE/GENEVE is found, include VNI in tag generation. When NVGRE is
02273                                                          found, include VSID. */
02274     uint64_t tag_gtp                      : 1;  /**< When GTP is parsed, include GTP's TEID in tag generation.
02275                                                          The GTP PKI_PCAM_TERM_E::L4_PORT PCAM entry must have
02276                                                          PKI_CL()_PCAM()_ACTION()[SETTY,ADVANCE]
02277                                                          be PKI_LTYPE_E::GTP,8 (ADVANCE needs to skip over the UDP header). */
02278     uint64_t tag_spi                      : 1;  /**< Include AH/ESP/GRE in tag generation.
02279                                                          0 = Exclude AH/ESP/GRE in tag generation.
02280                                                          1 = If IP SEC is parsed, include AH/ESP SPI field in tag generation, or if GRE
02281                                                          found, include GRE call number in tag generation. */
02282     uint64_t tag_syn                      : 1;  /**< Exclude source address for TCP SYN packets.
02283                                                          0 = Include source address if TAG_SRC_* used.
02284                                                          1 = Exclude source address for TCP packets with SYN & !ACK, even if TAG_SRC_* set. */
02285     uint64_t tag_pctl                     : 1;  /**< Include final IPv4 protocol or IPv6 next header in tag generation. */
02286     uint64_t tag_vs1                      : 1;  /**< When VLAN stacking is parsed, include second (network order) VLAN in tuple tag generation. */
02287     uint64_t tag_vs0                      : 1;  /**< When VLAN stacking is parsed, include first (network order) VLAN in tuple tag generation. */
02288     uint64_t tag_vlan                     : 1;  /**< Reserved. */
02289     uint64_t tag_mpls0                    : 1;  /**< Reserved. */
02290     uint64_t tag_prt                      : 1;  /**< Include interface port in tag hash. */
02291     uint64_t wqe_vs                       : 1;  /**< Which VLAN to put into PKI_WQE_S[VLPTR] when VLAN stacking.
02292                                                          0 = Use the first (in network order) VLAN or DSA VID.
02293                                                          1 = Use the second (in network order) VLAN. */
02294 #else
02295     uint64_t wqe_vs                       : 1;
02296     uint64_t tag_prt                      : 1;
02297     uint64_t tag_mpls0                    : 1;
02298     uint64_t tag_vlan                     : 1;
02299     uint64_t tag_vs0                      : 1;
02300     uint64_t tag_vs1                      : 1;
02301     uint64_t tag_pctl                     : 1;
02302     uint64_t tag_syn                      : 1;
02303     uint64_t tag_spi                      : 1;
02304     uint64_t tag_gtp                      : 1;
02305     uint64_t tag_vni                      : 1;
02306     uint64_t reserved_11_16               : 6;
02307     uint64_t qpg_port_msb                 : 4;
02308     uint64_t qpg_port_sh                  : 3;
02309     uint64_t qpg_qos                      : 3;
02310     uint64_t apad_nip                     : 3;
02311     uint64_t tt                           : 2;
02312     uint64_t reserved_32_63               : 32;
02313 #endif
02314     } s;

02322 /**
02323  * cvmx_pki_cl#_style#_cfg
02324  *
02325  * This register is inside PKI_CL()_SMEM(). These CSRs are used by
02326  * the PKI parse engine and other PKI hardware.
02327  *
02328  * For each legal j, PKI_CL(i)_STYLE(j)_CFG must be configured identically for i=0..1.
02329  */
02330 union cvmx_pki_clx_stylex_cfg {
02331     uint64_t u64;
02332     struct cvmx_pki_clx_stylex_cfg_s {
02333 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02334     uint64_t reserved_31_63               : 33;
02335     uint64_t ip6_udp_opt                  : 1;  /**< IPv6/UDP checksum is optional. IPv4 allows an optional UDP checksum by sending the all-0s
02336                                                          patterns. IPv6 outlaws this and the spec says to always check UDP checksum.
02337                                                          0 = Spec compliant, do not allow optional code.
02338                                                          1 = Treat IPv6 as IPv4; the all-0s pattern will cause a UDP checksum pass. */
02339     uint64_t lenerr_en                    : 1;  /**< L2 length error check enable. When set, the hardware checks that the number of packet
02340                                                          bytes following the L2 length field (excluding FCS) is at least as large as the L2
02341                                                          length field value whenever the Ethertype / L2 length field is <= 1535.
02342                                                          The PKI L2 length check assumes that the packet received by PKI contains a trailing FCS
02343                                                          when
02344                                                          the PKI_CL()_PKIND()_CFG[FCS_PRES] for the pkind of the packet is set. */
02345     uint64_t lenerr_eqpad                 : 1;  /**< Reserved. Must be zero. */
02346     uint64_t minmax_sel                   : 1;  /**< Selects which PKI_FRM_LEN_CHK() register is used for this pkind for MINERR and MAXERR
02347                                                          checks.
02348                                                          0 = use PKI_FRM_LEN_CHK(0).
02349                                                          1 = use PKI_FRM_LEN_CHK(1). */
02350     uint64_t maxerr_en                    : 1;  /**< Max frame error check enable. See PKI_FRM_LEN_CHK()[MAXLEN], [MINMAX_SEL],
02351                                                          PKI_OPCODE_E::L2_OVERSIZE,L2_OVERRUN, PKI_ERRLEV_E::LA, and PKI_WQE_S[ERRLEV,OPCODE]. */
02352     uint64_t minerr_en                    : 1;  /**< Min frame error check enable. See PKI_FRM_LEN_CHK()[MINLEN], [MINMAX_SEL],
02353                                                          PKI_OPCODE_E::L2_UNDERSIZE,L2_FRAGMENT, PKI_ERRLEV_E::LA, and PKI_WQE_S[ERRLEV,OPCODE]. */
02354     uint64_t qpg_dis_grptag               : 1;  /**< Disable computing group using PKI_WQE_S[TAG]. See PKI_WQE_S[GRP]. */
02355     uint64_t fcs_strip                    : 1;  /**< Strip L2 FCS bytes from packet, decrease PKI_WQE_S[LEN] by 4 bytes. Corresponding
02356                                                          PKI_CL()_PKIND()_CFG[FCS_PRES] must be set when [FCS_STRIP] is set.
02357                                                          See the PKI_OPCODE_E::L2_PUNY exception case. */
02358     uint64_t fcs_chk                      : 1;  /**< FCS checking enabled. Corresponding PKI_CL()_PKIND()_CFG[FCS_PRES] must be set
02359                                                          when [FCS_CHK] is set. See PKI_OPCODE_E::L2_PFCS,L2_FRAGMENT,L2_OVERRUN,
02360                                                          PKI_ERRLEV_E::LA, and PKI_WQE_S[ERRLEV,OPCODE]. */
02361     uint64_t rawdrp                       : 1;  /**< Allow RAW packet drop.
02362                                                          0 = Never drop packets with PKI_WQE_S[RAW] set.
02363                                                          1 = Allow the PKI to drop RAW packets based on PKI_AURA()_CFG[ENA_RED/ENA_DROP]. */
02364     uint64_t drop                         : 1;  /**< Force packet dropping.
02365                                                          0 = Drop packet based on PKI_AURA()_CFG[ENA_RED/ENA_DROP].
02366                                                          1 = Always drop the packet. Overrides [NODROP], [RAWDRP]. */
02367     uint64_t nodrop                       : 1;  /**< Disable QoS packet drop.
02368                                                          0 = Allowed to drop packet based on PKI_AURA()_CFG[ENA_RED/ENA_DROP].
02369                                                          1 = Never drop the packet. Overrides [RAWDRP]. */
02370     uint64_t qpg_dis_padd                 : 1;  /**< Disable computing port adder by QPG algorithm. See PKI_WQE_S[CHAN]. */
02371     uint64_t qpg_dis_grp                  : 1;  /**< Disable computing group by QPG algorithm.
02372                                                          [QPG_DIS_GRP] should normally always be clear. */
02373     uint64_t qpg_dis_aura                 : 1;  /**< Disable computing aura by QPG algorithm.
02374                                                          [QPG_DIS_AURA] should normally always be clear. */
02375     uint64_t reserved_11_15               : 5;
02376     uint64_t qpg_base                     : 11; /**< Base index into PKI_QPG_TBL(). */
02377 #else
02378     uint64_t qpg_base                     : 11;
02379     uint64_t reserved_11_15               : 5;
02380     uint64_t qpg_dis_aura                 : 1;
02381     uint64_t qpg_dis_grp                  : 1;
02382     uint64_t qpg_dis_padd                 : 1;
02383     uint64_t nodrop                       : 1;
02384     uint64_t drop                         : 1;
02385     uint64_t rawdrp                       : 1;
02386     uint64_t fcs_chk                      : 1;
02387     uint64_t fcs_strip                    : 1;
02388     uint64_t qpg_dis_grptag               : 1;
02389     uint64_t minerr_en                    : 1;
02390     uint64_t maxerr_en                    : 1;
02391     uint64_t minmax_sel                   : 1;
02392     uint64_t lenerr_eqpad                 : 1;
02393     uint64_t lenerr_en                    : 1;
02394     uint64_t ip6_udp_opt                  : 1;
02395     uint64_t reserved_31_63               : 33;
02396 #endif
02397     } s;
02398     struct cvmx_pki_clx_stylex_cfg_s      cn73xx;

02489                                                          See PKI_WQE_S[ERRLEV,OPCODE] and PKI_ERRLEV_E::LF. */
02490     uint64_t csum_le                      : 1;  /**< When set, PKI hardware performs an inner IPv4/IPv6 PKI_OPCODE_E::IP_CHK check (in an
02491                                                          IP-in-IP case) when PKI_LTYPE(PKI_WQE_S[LETY])_MAP[BELTYPE] equals either of
02492                                                          PKI_BELTYPE_E::IP4,IP6. PKI_WQE_S[LEPTR] points to the inner IPv4/IPv6 header in this
02493                                                          case. See PKI_WQE_S[ERRLEV,OPCODE] and PKI_ERRLEV_E::LE. */
02494     uint64_t csum_ld                      : 1;  /**< When set, PKI hardware performs an outer IPv4/IPv6 UDP PKI_OPCODE_E::L4_CHK
02495                                                          check (in an IP-in-IP case) when PKI_LTYPE(PKI_WQE_S[LDTY])_MAP[BELTYPE]
02496                                                          equals PKI_BELTYPE_E::UDP. PKI_WQE_S[LDPTR] points to the UDP header in this case.
02497                                                          See PKI_WQE_S[ERRLEV,OPCODE] and PKI_ERRLEV_E::LD. */
02498     uint64_t csum_lc                      : 1;  /**< When set, PKI hardware performs an outermost IPv4/IPv6 PKI_OPCODE_E::IP_CHK
02499                                                          check when PKI_LTYPE(PKI_WQE_S[LCTY])_MAP[BELTYPE] equals either of
02500                                                          PKI_BELTYPE_E::IP4,IP6. PKI_WQE_S[LCPTR] points to the IPv4/IPv6 header in this
02501                                                          case. See PKI_WQE_S[ERRLEV,OPCODE] and PKI_ERRLEV_E::LC. */
02502     uint64_t csum_lb                      : 1;  /**< Reserved. Must be zero. */
02503 #else
02504     uint64_t csum_lb                      : 1;
02505     uint64_t csum_lc                      : 1;
02506     uint64_t csum_ld                      : 1;
02507     uint64_t csum_le                      : 1;
02508     uint64_t csum_lf                      : 1;

02532 #endif

03092 /**
03093  * cvmx_pki_gbl_pen
03094  *
03095  * This register contains global configuration information that applies to all
03096  * pkinds. The values are opaque to PKI HW.
03097  *
03098  * This is intended for communication between the higher-level software SDK, and the
03099  * SDK code that loads PKI_IMEM() with the parse engine code. This allows the loader to
03100  * appropriately select the parse engine code with only those features required, so that
03101  * performance will be optimized.
03102  */
03103 union cvmx_pki_gbl_pen {
03104     uint64_t u64;
03105     struct cvmx_pki_gbl_pen_s {
03106 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03107     uint64_t reserved_10_63               : 54;
03108     uint64_t virt_pen                     : 1;  /**< Virtualization parsing enable.
03109                                                          0 = VXLAN/VXLANGPE/NVGRE/GENEVE is never used in any style. This enables internal power
03110                                                          and latency reductions.
03111                                                          1 = VXLAN/VXLANGPE/NVGRE/GENEVE parsing may be used.
03112                                                          See [L3_PEN] for supported [L3_PEN], [VIRT_PEN], [IL3_PEN], [L4_PEN,CLG_PEN] combinations. */
03113     uint64_t clg_pen                      : 1;  /**< Custom LG parsing enable.
03114                                                          0 = Custom LG is never used in any style; i.e. PKI_CL()_PKIND()_CFG[LG_CUSTOM_LAYER]
03115                                                          is zero for all indices. This enables internal power and latency reductions.
03116                                                          1 = Custom LG parsing may be used.
03117                                                          See [L3_PEN] for supported [L3_PEN], [VIRT_PEN], [IL3_PEN], [L4_PEN,CLG_PEN] combinations. */
03118     uint64_t cl2_pen                      : 1;  /**< Custom L2 parsing enable.
03119                                                          0 = Custom L2 is never used in any style; i.e. PKI_CL()_PKIND()_L2_CUSTOM[VALID]
03120                                                          is zero for all indices. This enables internal power and latency reductions.
03121                                                          1 = Custom L2 parsing may be used. */
03122     uint64_t l4_pen                       : 1;  /**< L4 parsing enable.
03123                                                          0 = L4 parsing is never used in any style. This enables internal power and latency
03124                                                          reductions.
03125                                                          1 = L4 parsing may be used.
03126                                                          See [L3_PEN] for supported [L3_PEN,VIRT_PEN,IL3_PEN,L4_PEN,CLG_PEN] combinations. */
03127     uint64_t il3_pen                      : 1;  /**< L3 inner parsing enable. Must be zero if L3_PEN is zero.
03128                                                          0 = L3 inner parsing is never used in any style. This enables internal power and latency
03129                                                          reductions.
03130                                                          1 = L3 inner (IP-in-IP) parsing may be used.
03131                                                          See [L3_PEN] for supported [L3_PEN,VIRT_PEN,IL3_PEN,L4_PEN,CLG_PEN] combinations. */
03132     uint64_t l3_pen                       : 1;  /**< L3 parsing enable.
03133                                                          0 = L3 parsing is never used in any style. This enables internal power and latency
03134                                                          reductions.
03135                                                          1 = L3 parsing may be used.
03136                                                          The supported [L3_PEN], [VIRT_PEN], [IL3_PEN], [L4_PEN,CLG_PEN] combinations are:
03137                                                          <pre>
03138                                                          L3_PEN VIRT_PEN IL3_PEN L4_PEN CLG_PEN
03139                                                          --------------------------------------
03140                                                            1       1        1      1       1
03141                                                            0       0        0      0       1
03142                                                            0       0        0      0       0
03143                                                          </pre> */
03144     uint64_t mpls_pen                     : 1;  /**< MPLS parsing enable.
03145                                                          0 = MPLS parsing is never used in any style; i.e. PKI_CL()_PKIND()_CFG[MPLS_EN]
03146                                                          is zero for all indices. This enables internal power and latency reductions.
03147                                                          1 = MPLS parsing may be used. */
03148     uint64_t fulc_pen                     : 1;  /**< Fulcrum parsing enable.
03149                                                          0 = Fulcrum parsing is never used in any style; i.e.
03150                                                          PKI_CL()_PKIND()_CFG[FULC_EN] is zero for all indices. This enables internal
03151                                                          power and latency reductions.
03152                                                          1 = Fulcrum parsing may be used. */
03153     uint64_t dsa_pen                      : 1;  /**< DSA parsing enable. Must be zero if HG_PEN is set.
03154                                                          0 = DSA parsing is never used in any style; i.e. PKI_CL()_PKIND()_CFG[DSA_EN] is
03155                                                          zero for all indices. This enables internal power and latency reductions.
03156                                                          1 = DSA parsing may be used. */
03157     uint64_t hg_pen                       : 1;  /**< HiGig parsing enable. Must be zero if DSA_PEN is set.
03158                                                          0 = HiGig parsing is never used in any style; i.e. PKI_CL()_PKIND()_CFG[HG2_EN,
03159                                                          HG_EN] are zero for all indices. This enables internal power and latency reductions.
03160                                                          1 = HiGig parsing may be used. */
03161 #else
03162     uint64_t hg_pen                       : 1;
03163     uint64_t dsa_pen                      : 1;
03164     uint64_t fulc_pen                     : 1;
03165     uint64_t mpls_pen                     : 1;
03166     uint64_t l3_pen                       : 1;
03167     uint64_t il3_pen                      : 1;
03168     uint64_t l4_pen                       : 1;
03169     uint64_t cl2_pen                      : 1;
03170     uint64_t clg_pen                      : 1;
03171     uint64_t virt_pen                     : 1;
03172     uint64_t reserved_10_63               : 54;
03173 #endif
03174     } s;
03175     struct cvmx_pki_gbl_pen_s             cn73xx;
03176     struct cvmx_pki_gbl_pen_s             cn78xx;
03177     struct cvmx_pki_gbl_pen_s             cn78xxp1;
03178     struct cvmx_pki_gbl_pen_s             cnf75xx;
03179 };
03180 typedef union cvmx_pki_gbl_pen cvmx_pki_gbl_pen_t;

03182 /**
03183  * cvmx_pki_gen_int
03184  */
03185 union cvmx_pki_gen_int {
03186     uint64_t u64;
03187     struct cvmx_pki_gen_int_s {
03188 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03189     uint64_t reserved_10_63               : 54;
03190     uint64_t bufs_oflow                   : 1;  /**< Set when PKI receives a packet that exceeds 256 buffers.
03191                                                          Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_BUFS_OFLOW. */
03192     uint64_t pkt_size_oflow               : 1;  /**< Set when PKI receives a packet that exceeds 64 KB.
03193                                                          Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_PKT_SIZE_OFLOW. */
03194     uint64_t x2p_req_ofl                  : 1;  /**< Set when a device attempts to have more than the allocated requests outstanding to PKI.
03195                                                          Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_X2P_REQ_OFL. */
03196     uint64_t drp_noavail                  : 1;  /**< Set when packet dropped due to no FPA pointers available for the aura the packet
03197                                                          requested. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_DRP_NOAVAIL. */
03198     uint64_t dat                          : 1;  /**< Set when data arrives before a SOP for the same reassembly ID for a packet. The first
03199                                                          detected
03200                                                          error associated with bits [DAT,SOP,EOP] of this register is only set here. A new bit can
03201                                                          be set when the previous reported bit is cleared. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_DAT. */
03202     uint64_t eop                          : 1;  /**< Set when an EOP is followed by an EOP for the same reassembly ID for a packet. The first
03203                                                          detected error associated with bits [DAT,EOP,SOP] of this register is only set here. A new
03204                                                          bit can be set when the previous reported bit is cleared. Also see PKI_PKT_ERR. Throws
03205                                                          PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_EOP. */
03206     uint64_t sop                          : 1;  /**< Set when a SOP is followed by an SOP for the same reassembly ID for a packet. The first
03207                                                          detected error associated with bits [DAT,EOP,SOP] of this register is only set here. A new
03208                                                          bit can be set when the previous reported bit is cleared. Also see PKI_PKT_ERR. Throws
03209                                                          PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_SOP. */
03210     uint64_t bckprs                       : 1;  /**< PKI asserted backpressure. Set when PKI was unable to accept the next valid data from
03211                                                          BGX/SRIO/DPI/LBK etc. over X2P due to all internal resources being used up, and PKI will
03212                                                          backpressure X2P. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_BCKPRS. */
03213     uint64_t crcerr                       : 1;  /**< PKI calculated bad CRC in the L2 frame. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_CRCERR. */
03214     uint64_t pktdrp                       : 1;  /**< Packet dropped due to QOS. If the QOS algorithm decides to drop a packet, PKI asserts this
03215                                                          interrupt. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_PKTDRP. */
03216 #else
03217     uint64_t pktdrp                       : 1;
03218     uint64_t crcerr                       : 1;
03219     uint64_t bckprs                       : 1;
03220     uint64_t sop                          : 1;
03221     uint64_t eop                          : 1;
03222     uint64_t dat                          : 1;
03223     uint64_t drp_noavail                  : 1;
03224     uint64_t x2p_req_ofl                  : 1;
03225     uint64_t pkt_size_oflow               : 1;
03226     uint64_t bufs_oflow                   : 1;
03227     uint64_t reserved_10_63               : 54;
03228 #endif
03229     } s;
03230     struct cvmx_pki_gen_int_s             cn73xx;
03231     struct cvmx_pki_gen_int_s             cn78xx;
03232     struct cvmx_pki_gen_int_cn78xxp1 {
03233 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03234     uint64_t reserved_8_63                : 56;
03235     uint64_t x2p_req_ofl                  : 1;  /**< Set when a device attempts to have more than the allocated requests outstanding to PKI.
03236                                                          Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_X2P_REQ_OFL. */
03237     uint64_t drp_noavail                  : 1;  /**< Set when packet dropped due to no FPA pointers available for the aura the packet
03238                                                          requested. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_DRP_NOAVAIL. */
03239     uint64_t dat                          : 1;  /**< Set when data arrives before a SOP for the same reassembly ID for a packet. The first
03240                                                          detected
03241                                                          error associated with bits [DAT,SOP,EOP] of this register is only set here. A new bit can
03242                                                          be set when the previous reported bit is cleared. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_DAT. */
03243     uint64_t eop                          : 1;  /**< Set when an EOP is followed by an EOP for the same reassembly ID for a packet. The first
03244                                                          detected error associated with bits [DAT,EOP,SOP] of this register is only set here. A new
03245                                                          bit can be set when the previous reported bit is cleared. Also see PKI_PKT_ERR. Throws
03246                                                          PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_EOP. */
03247     uint64_t sop                          : 1;  /**< Set when a SOP is followed by an SOP for the same reassembly ID for a packet. The first
03248                                                          detected error associated with bits [DAT,EOP,SOP] of this register is only set here. A new
03249                                                          bit can be set when the previous reported bit is cleared. Also see PKI_PKT_ERR. Throws
03250                                                          PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_SOP. */
03251     uint64_t bckprs                       : 1;  /**< PKI asserted backpressure. Set when PKI was unable to accept the next valid data from
03252                                                          BGX/ILK/DPI/LBK etc. over X2P due to all internal resources being used up, and PKI will
03253                                                          backpressure X2P. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_BCKPRS. */
03254     uint64_t crcerr                       : 1;  /**< PKI calculated bad CRC in the L2 frame. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_CRCERR. */
03255     uint64_t pktdrp                       : 1;  /**< Packet dropped due to QOS. If the QOS algorithm decides to drop a packet, PKI asserts this
03256                                                          interrupt. Throws PKI_INTSN_E::PKI_GEN_PKTDRP. */
03257 #else
03258     uint64_t pktdrp                       : 1;
03259     uint64_t crcerr                       : 1;
03260     uint64_t bckprs                       : 1;
03261     uint64_t sop                          : 1;
03262     uint64_t eop                          : 1;
03263     uint64_t dat                          : 1;
03264     uint64_t drp_noavail                  : 1;
03265     uint64_t x2p_req_ofl                  : 1;
03266     uint64_t reserved_8_63                : 56;
03267 #endif
03268     } cn78xxp1;
03269     struct cvmx_pki_gen_int_s             cnf75xx;
03270 };

03273 /**
03274  * cvmx_pki_icg#_cfg
03275  *
03276  * This register configures the cluster group.
03277  *
03278  */
03279 union cvmx_pki_icgx_cfg {
03280     uint64_t u64;
03281     struct cvmx_pki_icgx_cfg_s {
03282 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03283     uint64_t reserved_53_63               : 11;
03284     uint64_t maxipe_use                   : 5;  /**< Reserved. Must be 0x14. */
03285     uint64_t reserved_36_47               : 12;
03286     uint64_t clusters                     : 4;  /**< Reserved. Must be 0x3. */
03287     uint64_t reserved_27_31               : 5;
03288     uint64_t release_rqd                  : 1;  /**< Reserved. Must be zero. */
03289     uint64_t mlo                          : 1;  /**< Reserved. Must be zero. */
03290     uint64_t pena                         : 1;  /**< Parse enable. Must be set after PKI has been initialized and PKI_IMEM() loaded.
03291                                                          0 = IPE transitions from start directly to done without executing a sequence, and the KMEM
03292                                                          bits effectively are copied through to the WQ.
03293                                                          1 = Normal parse engine operation. */
03294     uint64_t timer                        : 12; /**< Current hold-off timer. Enables even spreading of cluster utilization over time;
03295                                                          while [TIMER] is nonzero, a cluster in this group will not start parsing. When a
03296                                                          cluster in this group starts parsing, [TIMER] is set to [DELAY], and decrements
03297                                                          every coprocessor-clock. [TIMER] is zeroed if all clusters in this group are
03298                                                          idle. */
03299     uint64_t delay                        : 12; /**< Delay between cluster starts, as described under TIMER. If 0x0, a cluster can
03300                                                          start at any time relative to other clusters. DELAY should typically be
03301                                                          the approximate parsing delay (800) divided by the number of bits set in
03302                                                          [CLUSTERS]. The smallest useful nonzero value is 0xA0,
03303                                                          corresponding to the minimum number of cycles needed to fill one cluster with
03304                                                          packets. So set [DELAY] = maximum(0xA0,800/number_of_clusters). */
03305 #else
03306     uint64_t delay                        : 12;
03307     uint64_t timer                        : 12;
03308     uint64_t pena                         : 1;
03309     uint64_t mlo                          : 1;
03310     uint64_t release_rqd                  : 1;
03311     uint64_t reserved_27_31               : 5;
03312     uint64_t clusters                     : 4;
03313     uint64_t reserved_36_47               : 12;
03314     uint64_t maxipe_use                   : 5;
03315     uint64_t reserved_53_63               : 11;
03316 #endif
03317     } s;
03318     struct cvmx_pki_icgx_cfg_s            cn73xx;
03319     struct cvmx_pki_icgx_cfg_s            cn78xx;

03321     struct cvmx_pki_icgx_cfg_s            cnf75xx;

03443                                                          match. Unpredictable unless [CONFLICT] is clear. */

03698  *
03699  * For diagnostic use only.
03700  *
03701  */
03702 union cvmx_pki_ptag_avail {
03703     uint64_t u64;
03704     struct cvmx_pki_ptag_avail_s {
03705 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03706     uint64_t reserved_8_63                : 56;
03707     uint64_t avail                        : 8;  /**< Number of ptags available for use. Decreasing the number of ptags will reduce
03708                                                          the number of packets waiting for parsing, which will lead to sooner
03709                                                          backpressure/packet drop, but will decrease the small-packet latency of PKI by
03710                                                          reducing buffer-bloat. AVAIL must be at least as great as the number of
03711                                                          reassembly IDs used by the system intends to use or the PTAGS can be exhausted
03712                                                          and PKI will hang. */
03713 #else
03714     uint64_t avail                        : 8;
03715     uint64_t reserved_8_63                : 56;
03716 #endif
03717     } s;
03718     struct cvmx_pki_ptag_avail_s          cn73xx;

03746 #else

03748     uint64_t aura_node                    : 2;

03755     uint64_t grptag_ok                    : 3;

03757     uint64_t reserved_60_63               : 4;
03758 #endif
03759     } s;

04442 /**
04443  * cvmx_pki_stat_ctl
04444  *
04445  * This register controls how the PKI statistics counters are handled.
04446  *
04447  */
04448 union cvmx_pki_stat_ctl {
04449     uint64_t u64;
04450     struct cvmx_pki_stat_ctl_s {
04451 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04452     uint64_t reserved_2_63                : 62;
04453     uint64_t mode                         : 2;  /**< The PKI_STAT*_X registers can be indexed either by port kind (pkind), or final style.
04454                                                          (Does not apply to the PKI_STAT_INB* nor PKI_DSTAT_* registers.)
04455                                                          _ 0x0 = X represents the packet's pkind.
04456                                                          _ 0x1 = X represents the low 6-bits of packet's final style.
04457                                                          _ 0x2 = X represents the packet's PKI_QPG_TBLB()[DSTAT_ID].
04458                                                            PKI_STAT()_STAT0..PKI_STAT()_STAT18 and PKI_STAT()_HIST0..PKI_STAT()_HIST6 will only
04459                                                            be incremented if the DSTAT_ID is less than 64; i.e. fits in the index of the
04460                                                            PKI_STAT()_STAT0 etc.
04461                                                          _ 0x3 = Reserved. */
04462 #else
04463     uint64_t mode                         : 2;
04464     uint64_t reserved_2_63                : 62;
04465 #endif
04466     } s;
04467     struct cvmx_pki_stat_ctl_s            cn73xx;
04468     struct cvmx_pki_stat_ctl_s            cn78xx;
04469     struct cvmx_pki_stat_ctl_s            cn78xxp1;
04470     struct cvmx_pki_stat_ctl_s            cnf75xx;
04471 };
04472 typedef union cvmx_pki_stat_ctl cvmx_pki_stat_ctl_t;
04473 
04474 /**
04475  * cvmx_pki_style#_buf
04476  *
04477  * This register configures the PKI BE skip amounts and other information.
04478  * It is indexed by final style, PKI_WQE_S[STYLE]<5:0>.
04479  */
04480 union cvmx_pki_stylex_buf {
04481     uint64_t u64;
04482     struct cvmx_pki_stylex_buf_s {
04483 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04484     uint64_t reserved_33_63               : 31;
04485     uint64_t pkt_lend                     : 1;  /**< Packet little-endian. Changes write operations of packet data to L2C to be in little-
04486                                                          endian. Does not change the WQE header format, which is properly endian neutral. */
04487     uint64_t wqe_hsz                      : 2;  /**< Work queue header size:
04488                                                          0x0 = WORD0..4, standard PKI_WQE_S. Note FIRST_SKIP may be set to not include WORD4 in
04489                                                          memory.
04490                                                          0x1 = WORD0..5.
04491                                                          0x2 = Reserved.
04492                                                          0x3 = Reserved.
04493                                                          Selects which parse engine words are transferred to the PKI BE. If a word is not
04494                                                          transferred and the word will reach memory (FIRST_SKIP is greater than that word
04495                                                          number), then the final WQE memory word will be zero, not the parse engine register
04496                                                          contents. */
04497     uint64_t wqe_skip                     : 2;  /**< WQE start offset. The number of 128-byte cache lines to skip between the buffer pointer
04498                                                          and WORD0 of the work-queue entry.
04499                                                          If [DIS_WQ_DAT]=1, legal values must satisfy:
04500                                                            * [MB_SIZE] >= (PKI_STYLE()_BUF[WQE_SKIP] * (128/8)) + 18
04501                                                          If [DIS_WQ_DAT]=0, legal values must satisfy:
04502                                                            * ([WQE_SKIP] * (128/8)) + 4 <= [FIRST_SKIP], to ensure the minimum of four
04503                                                              work-queue entry words will fit within [FIRST_SKIP]. */
04504     uint64_t first_skip                   : 6;  /**< The number of eight-byte words from the top of the first MBUF that the PKI stores the next
04505                                                          pointer.
04506                                                          If [DIS_WQ_DAT]=1, legal values must satisfy:
04507                                                            * [FIRST_SKIP] <= PKI_STYLE()_BUF[MB_SIZE] - 18.
04508                                                          If [DIS_WQ_DAT]=0, legal values must satisfy:
04509                                                            * [FIRST_SKIP] <= PKI_STYLE()_BUF[MB_SIZE] - 18.
04510                                                            * ([WQE_SKIP] * (128/8)) + X <= [FIRST_SKIP].
04511                                                            _ X must be at least 0x4 to ensure the minimum of four work-queue entry,
04512                                                              but 0x5 is recommended minimum. X = 0x4 will drop WQE WORD4, for use in
04513                                                              backward compatible applications. */
04514     uint64_t later_skip                   : 6;  /**< The number of eight-byte words from the top of any MBUF that is not the first MBUF that
04515                                                          PKI writes the next-pointer to. Legal values are 0 to PKI_STYLE()_BUF[MB_SIZE] - 18. */
04516     uint64_t opc_mode                     : 2;  /**< Select the style of write to the L2C.
04517                                                          0x0 = all packet data and next-buffer pointers are written through to memory.
04518                                                          0x1 = all packet data and next-buffer pointers are written into the cache.
04519                                                          0x2 = the first aligned cache block holding the WQE and/or front packet data are written
04520                                                          to
04521                                                          the L2 cache. All remaining cache blocks are not written to the L2 cache.
04522                                                          0x3 = the first two aligned cache blocks holding the WQE and front packet data are written
04523                                                          to the L2 cache. All remaining cache blocks are not written to the L2 cache. */
04524     uint64_t dis_wq_dat                   : 1;  /**< Separate first data buffer from the work queue entry.
04525                                                          0 = The packet link pointer will be at word [FIRST_SKIP] immediately followed by packet
04526                                                          data, in the same buffer as the work queue entry.
04527                                                          1 = The packet link pointer will be at word [FIRST_SKIP] in a new buffer separate from the
04528                                                          work queue entry. Words following the WQE in the same cache line will be zeroed, other
04529                                                          lines in the buffer will not be modified and will retain stale data (from the buffer's
04530                                                          previous use). This setting may decrease the peak PKI performance by up to half on small
04531                                                          packets. */
04532     uint64_t mb_size                      : 13; /**< The number of eight-byte words between the start of a buffer and the last word
04533                                                          that PKI may write into that buffer. The total amount of data stored by PKI into
04534                                                          the buffer will be MB_SIZE minus FIRST_SKIP or LATER_SKIP.
04535                                                          This must be even, in the range of 32 to 4096. This must be less than or equal
04536                                                          to the maximum size of every free page in every FPA pool this style may use.
04537                                                          If [DIS_WQ_DAT]=1, legal values must satisfy:
04538                                                            * MB_SIZE >= (PKI_STYLE()_BUF[WQE_SKIP] * (128/8)) + 18
04539                                                            * MB_SIZE >= PKI_STYLE()_BUF[FIRST_SKIP] + 18.
04540                                                            * MB_SIZE >= PKI_STYLE()_BUF[LATER_SKIP] + 18.
04541                                                          If [DIS_WQ_DAT]=0, legal values must satisfy:
04542                                                            * MB_SIZE >= PKI_STYLE()_BUF[FIRST_SKIP] + 18.
04543                                                            * MB_SIZE >= PKI_STYLE()_BUF[LATER_SKIP] + 18. */
04544 #else
04545     uint64_t mb_size                      : 13;
04546     uint64_t dis_wq_dat                   : 1;
04547     uint64_t opc_mode                     : 2;
04548     uint64_t later_skip                   : 6;
04549     uint64_t first_skip                   : 6;
04550     uint64_t wqe_skip                     : 2;
04551     uint64_t wqe_hsz                      : 2;
04552     uint64_t pkt_lend                     : 1;
04553     uint64_t reserved_33_63               : 31;
04554 #endif
04555     } s;
04556     struct cvmx_pki_stylex_buf_s          cn73xx;
04557     struct cvmx_pki_stylex_buf_s          cn78xx;
04558     struct cvmx_pki_stylex_buf_s          cn78xxp1;
04559     struct cvmx_pki_stylex_buf_s          cnf75xx;
04560 };
04561 typedef union cvmx_pki_stylex_buf cvmx_pki_stylex_buf_t;
04562 
04563 /**
04564  * cvmx_pki_style#_tag_mask
04565  *
04566  * This register configures the PKI BE tag algorithm.
04567  * It is indexed by final style, PKI_WQE_S[STYLE]<5:0>.
04568  */
04569 union cvmx_pki_stylex_tag_mask {
04570     uint64_t u64;
04571     struct cvmx_pki_stylex_tag_mask_s {
04572 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04573     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
04574     uint64_t mask                         : 16; /**< When set, each bit excludes corresponding bit of the tuple computed tag from being
04575                                                          included in the final tag. PKI_CL()_STYLE()_CFG2 [TAG_MASKEN] must be set. Does
04576                                                          not affect tags from packets with a PKI_INST_HDR_S when PKI_INST_HDR_S[UTAG] is set. */
04577 #else
04578     uint64_t mask                         : 16;
04579     uint64_t reserved_16_63               : 48;
04580 #endif
